. "Let $R$ be a commutative ring with identity and $\alpha \in
   R$. Then we have a ring homomorphism $\phi_{\alpha} : R 
   arrow R$ defined by \[ \phi_{\alpha} (p(x) ) = p( \alpha ) =
   a_n \alpha^n + \cdots + a_1 \alpha + a_0, \] where $p( x ) =
   a_n x^n + \cdots + a_1 x + a_0$."
